SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 133
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Robert Horace Everhart
of New Market.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Robert Horace Everhart; and
WHEREAS, Robert Everhart was a highly respected member of his community and a
consummate professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow
citizens in numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Everhart honorably served his country as a member of the U.S. Army
and retired as a carpenter from U.S. Steel, in which position he earned the respect and
admiration of his colleagues for the exemplary quality of his work; and
WHEREAS, after his retirement in the early 1990s, he could frequently be found around
the maintenance shop of Lost Creek Golf Club for many years afterwards, but his most prized
job, however, was being "Papaw" to his grandchildren, whom he loved so dearly; and
WHEREAS, a devout Christian, Robert Everhart was a longtime member of Paw Paw
Hollow Baptist Church. He loved "good gospel music" and enjoyed singing every chance he
could; one of the last songs he sang to his family was "I Won't Have to Worry Anymore"; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Everhart is survived by his son, Greg (Teresa) Everhart; bonus son,
Archie (Jennifer) Russell; grandchildren, Stacey (Shane) Carowick, Stephen Russell, and
Sirena (Nick) Williams; and great-grandchildren, Bella Grace, Clayton Russell, Jayla Robertson,
Baylor, and Emma Williams; and
WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his loving wife of seventy years, Ola Mae
Haworth Everhart; daughters, Janice Mae Everhart and Robin Everhart Russell; parents, J.F.
and Artie Everhart; brother, J.T. Everhart; and nephew, Jody Everhart; and
